When a teacher initiates the pupil*, who have undertaken the conventional practioes, he, on saking them bathe, should prepare a pasa mendala.
  Then he should spread a thread on the cast gust from the Middle of the thread, he should mark the East and the West aide equally&hellip;
  Then he should mark the north and the south side by a thread whose measurement should be the same, wh loh 18 already used for marking the eastern and western a irostions.
